- m.19 (Ab→Eb→Bb): Bass walks Ab2→Eb2→Bb2 descending P4s — idiomatic
  harp stepwise bass.
- m.28 (IV→I→V7): Ab2 LH (IV) drops a 5th to Eb2 (I), then Bb2 (V),
  elegant bass walk for final approach.
- m.29: Final root-position I with Eb2 bass — lowest pitch in piece,
  widest L-to-H span.

TEXTURE ARC:
